WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.800 --> 00:00:01.373
Ready.

00:00:01.373 --> 00:00:03.667
Hey, good morning family.

00:00:03.667 --> 00:00:04.820
Praise the Lord.

00:00:04.820 --> 00:00:06.850
Thank you for joining us again today.

00:00:06.850 --> 00:00:08.300
We're excited to be here.

00:00:08.300 --> 00:00:10.880
We have some things on our heart to pray about.

00:00:10.880 --> 00:00:17.404
There are so many of you already here is what I want to say, but we're excited to see you all.

00:00:17.768 --> 00:00:22.960
We went to a Billy Burke healing service this week.

00:00:22.960 --> 00:00:23.920
That's where we were.

00:00:23.920 --> 00:00:27.360
If everybody wanted to know, they're like, "How come you're not posting videos?

00:00:27.360 --> 00:00:28.640
" Well, we're getting refreshed.

00:00:28.640 --> 00:00:34.560
And we went down to Fort Worth to see Billy Burke, and it was wonderful.

00:00:34.560 --> 00:00:37.828
You know, we had great expectations.

00:00:37.828 --> 00:00:38.674
We did.

00:00:38.674 --> 00:00:42.231
I told her, "Man, I cannot wait to go.

00:00:42.231 --> 00:00:46.924
" The first night when we went, we saw so many of you all.

00:00:46.924 --> 00:00:55.280
I mean, there were so many people that came from all over the United States to say hello to us and come to the service and everything.

00:00:55.280 --> 00:01:05.771
So, you know, with me and Diana, I told her, I said, "I'm not used to being in public and people knowing who I am, especially in a church that's that big.

00:01:07.383 --> 00:01:10.250
" Everybody came up trying to introduce themselves.

00:01:11.240 --> 00:01:17.520
I'm a person who is already discerning; I'm trying to see if you're a friend or a foe.

00:01:17.956 --> 00:01:21.930
Are you here to be nice to me, or are you going to come against me?

00:01:21.930 --> 00:01:24.103
So I'm looking at people's eyes.

00:01:24.949 --> 00:01:32.937
When there are that many coming, and it's that much of a flood, and I'm having that much of a download trying to find—I told Braden, "That was really awkward," because I'm not used to that.

00:01:35.679 --> 00:01:44.609
Trying to shake everybody's hand and discern what's going on with them, I told Diana, "I'm going to have to practice a lot because I'm not used to it.

00:01:44.609 --> 00:01:45.699
" We're hermits, y'all.

00:01:45.699 --> 00:01:48.700
We stay at home a lot because of our daughter.

00:01:48.700 --> 00:01:55.253
You know, she has special needs she's overcoming, so I'm not used to going out and being in a big crowd like that.

00:01:55.467 --> 00:02:02.620
Our little church that we have there in Collinsville only has probably four or five hundred people there on a Sunday.

00:02:02.620 --> 00:02:07.573
But when you have thousands of people in an auditorium, it's a big difference for us.

00:02:07.573 --> 00:02:10.368
But it was so nice to meet you all.

00:02:10.368 --> 00:02:17.120
And I want to say, if you're there, I know it's exciting to see us, but I want to tell you, we're just Brandon and Diana.

00:02:17.410 --> 00:02:21.813
We appreciate all the honor, and we pray for every single one of you if you want prayer.

00:02:21.813 --> 00:02:29.093
But like I said, there were so many people at one time, I told her, "I don't know how to do that next time," trying to go through everything.

00:02:30.926 --> 00:02:42.250
But if you came out there and we prayed for you, where I'm going with that is: if you got prayer and you were in that service, did you receive your healing?

00:02:43.650 --> 00:02:47.120
I'm excited to hear, because there were some people that had strokes, folks.

00:02:47.120 --> 00:02:53.840
And there were some people battling depression and all kinds of different things that they were going through that they needed a miracle.

00:02:53.840 --> 00:02:56.491
They needed a breakthrough in their life.

00:02:57.172 --> 00:02:58.932
It was exciting to see them.

00:02:59.226 --> 00:03:00.587
I'm believing that they got touched.

00:03:00.587 --> 00:03:11.509
There was one lady, folks, who got touched so much that she could hardly drive home, and she was supposed to help navigate her husband clear back to Austin, Texas.

00:03:11.509 --> 00:03:15.640
And she didn't know—she was like she was on another planet.

00:03:15.640 --> 00:03:20.151
I'm talking about, she had the Holy Ghost all over her.

00:03:20.680 --> 00:03:22.080
It was amazing, wasn't it?

00:03:22.080 --> 00:03:22.480
Yeah.

00:03:22.480 --> 00:03:25.220
And really nice people from Estonia.

00:03:25.220 --> 00:03:26.959
Is that right?

00:03:28.346 --> 00:03:28.693
Estonia.

00:03:28.693 --> 00:03:29.760
Braden remembers.

00:03:29.760 --> 00:03:33.074
But like I said, there were people coming from everywhere.

00:03:33.074 --> 00:03:36.700
But I just wanted to say thank you all, always, for being so kind.

00:03:49.519 --> 00:03:49.821
To the people from Houston I met who had an air duct system business, they're such a blessing, and we pray over them and so many people.

00:04:00.444 --> 00:04:00.640
We met the people with the dogs, you know, so it was really interesting.

00:04:00.640 --> 00:04:07.303
It's kind of like our public debut in a sense, since the ministry is really growing, to go out and meet everybody.

00:04:07.303 --> 00:04:11.149
But I want to keep kicking that down the road.

00:04:18.799 --> 00:04:19.119
I mean, we can go over things, but one of the things is really cool.

00:04:19.119 --> 00:04:21.360
Now, I have to go back.

00:04:21.360 --> 00:04:23.360
Let me back it up a little bit.

00:04:23.360 --> 00:04:32.000
As we were sitting in the back—because the Lord told me, before all this happened, on Wednesday before we left, I was overcoming big time and I was under attack.

00:04:34.080 --> 00:04:34.400
I didn't feel good at all.

00:04:36.267 --> 00:04:41.383
And I told D, "I feel too sick to go.

00:04:42.754 --> 00:04:47.152
I don't feel like we should go.

00:04:47.152 --> 00:04:52.537
" And she said, "Okay, well, whatever you want to do, babe," like she always is—she's always so supportive.

00:04:55.392 --> 00:04:55.616
And I told her, I said, "Let's pray.

00:04:55.616 --> 00:04:58.045
" And the Lord said, "Brandon, it's a healing service.

00:04:58.045 --> 00:04:59.062
Go expect your miracle.

00:05:04.754 --> 00:05:05.063
" And I said, "Yeah, well, duh.

00:05:05.063 --> 00:05:06.137
We'll go.

00:05:13.280 --> 00:05:13.510
" And so I went and I drove.

00:05:17.160 --> 00:05:17.390
It was a long drive.

00:05:19.520 --> 00:05:20.240
And I told her, I said, "I'm overcoming so bad right now.

00:05:20.240 --> 00:05:23.950
I'm going to have to pull over to the side of the road.

00:05:26.070 --> 00:05:26.300
" And so I just kept driving by faith.

00:05:26.300 --> 00:05:33.623
I kept standing, I kept quoting the word, I kept believing, just like I teach you all.

00:05:36.079 --> 00:05:36.399
I was practicing what I preach.

00:05:38.000 --> 00:05:47.985
And I got there expecting, but the first night I did not feel the presence of the Lord as strong as what I was wanting, you know, and I'm not disappointed.

00:05:47.985 --> 00:05:49.643
It's not Billy Burke's fault.

00:05:49.643 --> 00:05:51.769
No, it's my receptor, where I was at.

00:05:55.828 --> 00:05:57.579
I'm going into the atmosphere, and it wasn't—you know.

00:05:57.579 --> 00:06:01.929
So the Lord said, "Brandon, I want you to fast.

00:06:03.920 --> 00:06:04.880
" And I said, "You want me to fast?

00:06:06.600 --> 00:06:06.790
" I said, "Okay, for how long?

00:06:06.790 --> 00:06:07.620
" "Until that night.

00:06:08.920 --> 00:06:09.180
" I said, "Well, that's great.

00:06:09.180 --> 00:06:10.526
Okay, well, I'll do it.

00:06:23.164 --> 00:06:33.829
" So I started praying, I started fasting, and the next morning, I woke up and I went to the service, and the glory came on me, and I felt the power of God hit me.

00:06:50.400 --> 00:06:50.740
I'm telling you, I started feeling all the symptoms start lifting off of me.

00:06:52.780 --> 00:06:53.120
I started feeling completely healed.

00:06:57.067 --> 00:07:01.599
And I'm telling you, folks, the night before, it was like you could feel it in the atmosphere, and I was hearing it in the spirit realm.

00:07:05.939 --> 00:07:06.209
I don't know if this was something new for me.

00:07:12.720 --> 00:07:13.740
I told Diana, "This is like something because I'm listening, but I can hear things and what the Lord's showing me.

00:07:16.684 --> 00:07:16.933
Is this fake?

00:07:16.933 --> 00:07:17.910
This is real.

00:07:17.910 --> 00:07:19.290
This is what I'm hearing.

00:07:22.594 --> 00:07:25.226
" And you know me, I am so huge on miracles and the glory and the manifestation of everything.

00:07:25.226 --> 00:07:30.416
But I was hearing in the atmosphere the thoughts of—I don't know if it's other people around me or what—"Is this fake?

00:07:44.340 --> 00:07:44.600
Is this made up?

00:07:54.266 --> 00:07:54.560
Is this performance?

00:07:58.091 --> 00:07:58.446
" And it was bombarding my thoughts.

00:07:59.376 --> 00:08:01.140
And the Lord said, "Take authority over the atmosphere.

00:08:01.900 --> 00:08:02.340
" And I thought, "That's interesting.

00:08:02.340 --> 00:08:05.599
What are you showing me?

00:08:05.599 --> 00:08:08.435
" Because you know me, I'm always a student.

00:08:08.435 --> 00:08:11.919
Diana and I are always students.

00:08:17.160 --> 00:08:17.370
We don't have everything figured out, but we want to learn.

00:08:24.506 --> 00:08:24.693
And I told her, as we're listening and we're hearing, what are we hearing in the spiritual atmosphere of this auditorium right now?

00:08:28.770 --> 00:08:29.140
And I was hearing, "Is this fake?

00:08:29.140 --> 00:08:30.620
Is this performance?

00:08:30.620 --> 00:08:31.771
Is this authentic?

00:08:31.771 --> 00:08:32.594
" All these things.

00:08:34.133 --> 00:08:36.349
And it was coming, and I personally know this man.

00:08:43.200 --> 00:08:43.600
And I'm like, "Of course it is.

00:08:43.600 --> 00:08:49.856
" And I started coming against that, and I was like, "That is demonic," but it was coming against your thoughts.

00:09:02.959 --> 00:09:03.119
And as I'm standing in the back, and that's when I went into the next day and it was still lingering.

00:09:03.119 --> 00:09:07.007
That's when the Lord told me, "I want you to fast and pray over this atmosphere.

00:09:07.007 --> 00:09:14.649
" Well, I went in, and we drove around like we do all the time here in Tulsa, driving around our area praying.

00:09:26.136 --> 00:09:26.285
Well, I drove around Fort Worth for about seven hours after the service.

00:09:26.285 --> 00:09:28.650
My goodness, they've got a lot of work to do.

00:09:28.650 --> 00:09:34.720
I'm not used to a major city like that.

00:09:34.720 --> 00:09:51.290
Sitting in traffic is like going to Tampa, but we were just praying over Fort Worth as we went through there, interceding and praying for the glory to come on that city, praying for a major harvest of souls in the really rough areas.

00:09:51.290 --> 00:09:57.712
Well, as we did that, I started feeling the atmosphere change and was just praying for that meeting that night.

00:09:57.712 --> 00:10:00.853
When we got to the meeting that night, it was packed.

00:10:05.360 --> 00:10:09.080
But we sat in the back because the Lord said, 'I want you to sit in the back and pray over this service.

00:10:09.080 --> 00:10:14.106
' So, we sat towards the back, and Diana and I were just interceding.

00:10:14.106 --> 00:10:18.889
We started praying, and you could feel the tangible presence of God; it was so heavy.

00:10:18.889 --> 00:10:26.240
Both of us, at the exact same time, felt a crown, like a glory, come over our heads at the exact same time.

00:10:27.570 --> 00:10:30.907
I looked at her and said, 'I just felt like a helmet of glory came on my head.

00:10:30.907 --> 00:10:35.120
' And she said, 'Brandon, I felt it too.

00:10:35.120 --> 00:10:37.560
' It was amazing, and I felt the glory.

00:10:37.560 --> 00:10:41.609
While I was in the back, the Lord said, 'Receive your healing.

00:10:42.940 --> 00:10:43.600
You don't have to have anybody touch you.

00:10:43.600 --> 00:10:44.857
Practice what you preach.

00:10:44.857 --> 00:10:51.480
' There are so many people who think you have to have someone lay hands on you to receive.

00:10:51.480 --> 00:10:52.040
No.

00:10:57.520 --> 00:10:58.264
When you're in the atmosphere of glory, and the presence of the Lord is there, receive what you're believing for.

00:10:58.432 --> 00:10:59.440
And the Lord said, 'Believe big.

00:10:59.440 --> 00:11:00.400
Believe big.

00:11:00.400 --> 00:11:13.200
' Even if you're in a service like that and everyone else is getting prayed for, and you feel like you're the only one who isn't, believe God for big things right where you're at.

00:11:13.200 --> 00:11:22.377
I'm telling you, it's time to believe Him for big things—exceedingly, abundantly, above all that you dare ask or think.

00:11:22.377 --> 00:11:28.640
So, I was sitting back, the power of God came on me, and I was healed.

00:11:28.640 --> 00:11:35.182
I'm making this story too long, but after that happened, we were sitting in there and Diana said, 'I can see the mist.

00:11:40.224 --> 00:11:40.496
I can see the mist.

00:11:40.496 --> 00:11:42.420
' Tell them, babe.

00:11:42.420 --> 00:11:48.800
Yeah, we were sitting in the very back, and I could see this light mist coming all into the room.

00:11:48.800 --> 00:11:55.359
You know, when you're in that atmosphere and sitting in it, you don't realize it until it's right on you.

00:11:59.280 --> 00:12:02.910
I started looking, and I was like, 'There's a haze in here that wasn't here when we first walked in, right?

00:12:02.910 --> 00:12:06.560
' And then, all of a sudden, all the fire alarms went off.

00:12:11.800 --> 00:12:14.760
We have video of it.

00:12:16.079 --> 00:12:19.380
I told Braden to tape it—we can't play it because he doesn't have it downloaded yet.

00:12:19.380 --> 00:12:26.679
But as we could see the mist, the glory, the presence of the Lord started coming in so strong.

00:12:26.679 --> 00:12:38.980
There was a man with cerebral palsy whose hands were all crippled up when he got up there, and the power of God hit his hands and they started straightening out.

00:12:38.980 --> 00:12:41.600
He said, 'I haven't been able to ever do this.

00:12:41.600 --> 00:12:44.120
' I'm telling you, this guy's faith was off the charts.

00:12:51.156 --> 00:12:51.511
It melted me because here he is, severely handicapped in the natural, giving God praise for where he's at in his life.

00:12:54.880 --> 00:12:57.143
It made me think, 'What do you ever have to complain about when you see somebody overcome?

00:12:57.143 --> 00:13:00.937
' He was in the midst of his storm, praising God to the point that it challenged me.

00:13:11.540 --> 00:13:11.880
That was good.

00:13:11.880 --> 00:13:13.240
It was beautiful.

00:13:13.240 --> 00:13:24.320
We saw so many other people who were believing God for a breakthrough, or for many different things—lumps in their chests and all kinds of things get healed—and it was just wonderful.

00:13:24.320 --> 00:13:36.720
But as those fire alarms were going off, I do have to make a disclaimer here: I do not know what caused the fire alarms to go off in the service, whether somebody pulled the alarm or whatever.

00:13:36.720 --> 00:13:44.000
But we did know before it ever went off, Diana and I both said, 'You can feel the glory; it's in the atmosphere.

00:13:44.960 --> 00:13:47.080
You can see a mist or a fog in here.

00:13:47.080 --> 00:13:55.215
' Later, the fire alarms started going off all throughout the building, and it was live.

00:14:01.911 --> 00:14:02.196
I told D, 'Did the glory smoke just set off the fire alarm in the church?

00:14:02.196 --> 00:14:08.880
' I think it did, but you don't want to say that because somebody could have pulled the alarm.

00:14:08.880 --> 00:14:15.920
But between us thousands of people, I want to say it was the glory that set off that fire alarm.

00:14:16.133 --> 00:14:19.422
It was just too cool because I didn't want to be hyperspiritual or try to create sensationalism.

00:14:19.422 --> 00:14:22.737
I just know I'm expecting God to do something big, aren't you?

00:14:22.737 --> 00:14:26.891
I'm expecting God to show up and show off in this month of September.

00:14:34.320 --> 00:14:34.507
The Lord told me as I was sitting there, 'Brandon, what you're seeing is a spiritual arsonist.

00:14:34.507 --> 00:14:38.376
Billy Burke is a spiritual arsonist; he goes and causes fires in these services.

00:14:38.376 --> 00:14:48.868
' And He said, 'This is what I want you to be—a spiritual arsonist for the Lord, causing fires by the Holy Ghost, stirring people up, and getting them ready for the soon return of the Lord Jesus Christ.

00:14:48.868 --> 00:14:57.429
' It's time for you to be excited because God is about to show up and show off in your life, and I want you to believe Him for big things tonight.

00:15:04.950 --> 00:15:05.160
I want you to believe Him that what's impossible in your life will soon become possible.

00:15:05.160 --> 00:15:11.051
I'm just believing right now with you for your miracle, for your creative miracle, whatever you may need in your life.

00:15:11.051 --> 00:15:15.360
I told Diana, 'I'm tired of always having this attitude of, well, we're just waiting for it to happen.

00:15:15.360 --> 00:15:17.093
We're ready for the manifestation now.

00:15:17.093 --> 00:15:19.724
' And Billy Burke said something really cool about it.

00:15:19.724 --> 00:15:22.183
Braden, tell them what he said about the grocery cart.

00:15:22.183 --> 00:15:30.000
Yeah, the analogy he had was amazing because he was saying how people don't have that bulldog tenacity about their healing and what Jesus did for us on the cross.

00:15:30.000 --> 00:15:36.320
He said whenever you go into a grocery store, you put all your groceries in that cart.

00:15:40.000 --> 00:15:41.680
You don't own the cart, and you don't own the groceries yet—you haven't even paid for them.

00:15:41.680 --> 00:15:46.389
But if somebody walks up and tries to push your cart away, you're like, 'Hey, that's mine!

00:15:46.389 --> 00:15:51.074
' You will fight them over that, but you don't even own it yet.

00:15:51.074 --> 00:15:57.839
So, that's what he was saying: it's not even yours yet, but Jesus already paid it all.

00:15:57.839 --> 00:16:03.040
Since He paid the price, we should have that same bulldog tenacity of faith over our healing.

00:16:07.920 --> 00:16:08.144
I thought it was an amazing analogy.

00:16:08.144 --> 00:16:30.727
Even when you don't have the full manifestation yet—it's like you don't have the groceries in your house yet, you just have them in your buggy and you're pushing them around—if someone came up and tried to grab your bread or your eggs out of that cart, you'd go, 'Hey, hold on, those are my eggs!

00:16:30.727 --> 00:16:35.786
' You haven't even purchased them yet, but you're bold enough to tell people, 'Those are my eggs.

00:16:35.786 --> 00:16:39.120
' Well, I want you to look at your healing the same way.

00:16:39.120 --> 00:16:40.240
That's my healing.

00:16:40.240 --> 00:16:41.760
Yes, that's my deliverance.

00:16:43.1000 --> 00:16:48.213
You may not have the full manifestation of what you're believing God for, ladies and gentlemen, but you got to have that.

00:16:48.213 --> 00:16:51.816
That's mine regardless if I'm seeing it or walking in the fruit of it.

00:16:51.816 --> 00:16:54.416
What's in my spiritual cart belongs to me.

00:16:54.832 --> 00:16:58.026
I have this, and I'm going to walk in it because God paid the price.

00:16:58.026 --> 00:17:01.657
Jesus paid the price for you to walk in total victory in your life.

00:17:01.657 --> 00:17:02.891
He paid the price.

00:17:02.891 --> 00:17:05.120
Nothing's too big, and nothing's too small.

00:17:05.120 --> 00:17:08.360
Jesus paid the price for you to have it all.

00:17:10.616 --> 00:17:13.165
And we allow the enemy to come in and try to rob us, even like what I was doing on Wednesday.

00:17:13.165 --> 00:17:16.149
Yeah, I don't want to go to the healing service.

00:17:16.149 --> 00:17:16.731
I'm overcoming.

00:17:16.731 --> 00:17:17.771
It's a healing service.

00:17:22.731 --> 00:17:23.166
And I was like, 'You know, okay, believe God in the healing service.

00:17:23.166 --> 00:17:25.771
' And so we went.

00:17:29.520 --> 00:17:32.674
And so, you know, it's just trying to go through these things and say, 'You know what?

00:17:32.674 --> 00:17:34.009
We got it.

00:17:34.009 --> 00:17:35.022
We can believe God, too.

00:17:35.022 --> 00:17:36.000
' Just like this.

00:17:47.900 --> 00:17:48.270
You know what I'm saying?

00:17:48.270 --> 00:17:56.039
What I'm trying to do is paint it to you all that Brandon and Diana are believing just like you all are.

00:17:56.039 --> 00:17:59.039
We're just believing for stuff just like you all are.

00:17:59.039 --> 00:18:06.640
And when I'm overcoming in my body, and my flesh wanted to lay in bed and feel sorry for myself, the Lord said, 'I want you to do this.

00:18:08.559 --> 00:18:10.103
I want you to go by faith.

00:18:18.360 --> 00:18:18.630
I want you to speak to it.

00:18:18.630 --> 00:18:21.147
' And it wasn't something that was contagious.

00:18:21.147 --> 00:18:25.223
I was overcoming something with my own flesh.

00:18:25.760 --> 00:18:32.773
And you know, it's like, 'Well, thanks a lot for spreading your bug around.

00:18:32.773 --> 00:18:33.999
' No, it wasn't a bug.

00:18:33.999 --> 00:18:38.640
It wasn't anything like that.

00:18:38.640 --> 00:18:41.180
It was something I was overcoming.

00:18:41.180 --> 00:18:45.800
And so I told Diana, I said, 'Let's do this by faith.

00:18:45.800 --> 00:18:47.429
' And we did it.

00:19:01.920 --> 00:19:02.320
And I got what I was believing for.

00:19:07.600 --> 00:19:08.027
And it's the glory.

00:19:08.027 --> 00:19:09.257
The glory.

00:19:21.180 --> 00:19:21.510
And I'm telling you, we're never looking for a person.

00:19:21.510 --> 00:19:25.359
I'm going to tell you this: it's not the person, it's Jesus.

00:19:26.159 --> 00:19:27.288
And Jesus shows up.

00:19:27.653 --> 00:19:33.409
